<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-837-346  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 837 346.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  Sept 10 1990 v24 n37 p101(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>CA loses moral victory to employee. (Computer AssociatesInternational Inc., Patrick Navin)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Booker, Ellis.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Patrick Navin won a $6,216 judgement against the softwarepublisher Computer Associates International Inc for laying him offafter acquiring Uccel Corp, where he worked.andP;  An Illinois circuitcourt decided that Computer Associates (CA) violated a personnelpolicy regarding severance pay implemented by Uccel before theacquisition.andP;  Three hundred Uccel employees were dismissed, as wasNavin although he was on vacation at the time.andP;  CA contended hewas offered a position at CA that he refused.andP;  The company'slawyer believes the court was incorrect in its interpretation ofthe law and that Uccel implemented the severance pay policy as a'parachute' without CA's knowledge or consent.andP;  CA decided not toappeal the decision because of the small amount involved.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Computer Associates International Inc. (personnel management).andO;Ticker:    CA.andO;Topic:     Law SuitPersonnel ProblemsEmploymentContractsFirings.andO;Person:    Navin, Patrick (cases).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>